info: Windmill is like Christmas for the Danes. You gotta go. And you look forward to it for months. This year we are bringing a women's national team  that is to some extent based on the team that played EUC2015. But this year we will be adding some talents who have not previously been on a national roster, but none the less are great assets and well known from the club scene. We have also gathered some weapons from the former Master team as Danish ladies don't seem to age or retire. Ever. This mix of young and less young players gives the team a nice glow of love for the game, good spirit and high intensity. And everybody works like h... to make the Danish Kingdom proud. Windmill will be the last tournament before WUGC and we are excited to show how far we have been able to take this team. We will be coached by the playing coach Maya Mileck - a player who needs little to no introduction.

info:
4 handed. Wild as monkeys. And we paint with all the colours of the wind.

Having taken off in 2009, we have been competing in Polish championships and other tournaments, both domestic and international, regularly ever since. We have played outdoor, indoor and beach ultimate in all corners of Poland, but also: Lithuania, the Czech Republic, Hungary, Germany, Belgium (G-Spot) and Ireland (Golden Cup). We arrived 4th at EUCR-E Mixed 2014, 6th at Polish Mixed Championships in 2014 and 9th in 2015. We see ourselves as a thoroughly mixed team, with girls playing a crucial role on the field, but at times we also participate in open/women events. 4hands Women took 2nd place at Polish Women Championships in 2013 and were 3rd twice, in 2013 and 2016 at Józbee – the longest running Polish indoor tournament. We had our people in all Polish national teams (mixed, open and women) at European Championships 2015 in Copenhagen. We aim at improving our initial seeding and showing best spirit at all of the tournaments we attend and most of 
the times we succeed.
name: Test 4hands

info:

Our complete disregard for our own limitations brought us to a 9th place at last years windmill. This year we hope to be back and do even better, as we have still have no regard for what we can't do!

We’re not saying that Oy Vey has been of paramount importance in keeping peace between the two nations, but one of our cutters did major in public relations. 
“Oy vey,” the phrase, was adopted from Yiddish, harkening back to the roots of many of the players. 
Notable accomplishments include formation of the team in 2015, reformation of the team in 2016, and throwing two Callaghans in one game.

info: Rubik's Cube was founded over a year ago by a group of friends. We all love playing Frisbee and together we want to play in a team that combines competitive ultimate with highest standards in spirit and party durability. This particular composition makes us a unique team, with every player handpicked by the core members. Playing a tournament with Rubik's Cube involves high-quality mixed ultimate on the field and colorful morph suits, glittery body paint, bare skin and heaps of ice cubes off the fields. We like to make every tournament as much fun and excitement as possible for players as well as spectators. You want to see the Cubes in action? - Here we go: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d2fErH3EoN0&feature;=youtu.be

info: When you first see us we're shiny and fast. You show us off to your friends and take us all over town. Then comes the rain and cold. The seasons change, years go by. Eventually you notice a squeaking, something comes loose, speed not as remarkable as it once was. The rust starts to settle in. You try to stop it, make a few adjustments, replace some aging parts. In the end, there is nothing you can do. We're Rusty Bikes. We're everywhere. You think we're done but we keep coming back. And of course... we're a hell of a fun ride!
name: Test Rusty Bikes

The team consists of close friends, mostly out of our homemade junior program and it is well-known for its passion and high spirit on the field as well as its party moves no matter if at night or breakfast-time. Catchup's philosophy is to educate and train high-level Ultimate from a young age in order to successfully implement them into their rosters already in early years. A young, committed and athletic but also very well-spirited team dedicated to the game of Ultimate is the result - already for years now.
Have fun and sing with those skilled boys, but beware of the hammer!

info: Well, we are a bunch of Crazy Dogs, that's for sure. We're loud, sniffling around everywhere, sticking around long and close together all day long. We like food and drinks, lying on the ground, and yes, if you toss us Frisbee, we might catch it. Don't expect us to throw it back though, we like to keep our discs if possible. We are quite easy to handle Dogs, we are family friendly and we like cats, too. There is no record of any Crazy Dog ever having bitten somebody. If it ever happens, remember: We just wanted to play!
